Details

Job Posting Title:   SE_Product Planner_Specialist
Description:   Volvo Trucks Heavy Duty Product Planner and Industry Vertical Analyst

Who we are

At Strategic Product Planning, within Group Truck Technology, we navigate the transformation and set the direction through a visionary Strategic Product Plan supporting the Group’s long-term ambitions. We bring value through our industry knowledge, we leverage holistic thinking, bringing clarity and visibility towards a competitive Product and Service offer.
Within SPP, our team is responsible to the product plan development for Volvo Trucks and Renault Trucks Heavy Cab Over engine platform. Composed of 12 people, we come from different horizon and site (Lyon, Göteborg and Curitiba), we are brave and inclusive, passionate about inspiring the organization towards the future.

Job description
o       Industry verticals (Market studies) investigations
       Describe an industrial segment on macro level, including market size, mega trends, main stakeholders etc..
       Describe emerging trends and innovations in this segment.
       Identify stakeholders pain points or source of advantage along the value chain.
       Evaluate decarbonization journey of the industry, investigate transport logistic flow using connected vehicle data, estimate potential logistic change and impact of transported good cost by using Zero Emission Vehicles.

o       Be involved in development project as SPP representative (Prerequisites, vehicle volume, Variant volume matrix…).
       Truck market investigations, internet search and data analysis.
       Analyze truck sales as a base of volume estimation for projects.
       Support the product and services plan updates and contribute to establish new product events.

Occasional travels in France and abroad may happen.

Skills essential for the assignment:
•       Professional English is absolutely mandatory.
•       Knowledge of the truck market and products.
•       Data analysis and internet search tools.
•       Knowledge of Volvo product documentation tool Kola
•       Financial knowledge and business orientation is considered as a plus.
•       We seek an autonomous and energetic person who is able to take initiative and capable to perform in an international cross-functional environment.

Expected Education Level
•       Engineering degree (MSc or equivalent, BAC +5)

Location
The location of the position is Goteborg, Sweden

Date of application : From 8/1/2024
Duration : 1 year (Extensible)

Specialist: position typically requires 8 years or more relevant experience

Volvo Group is an equal opportunity employer that values diversity in our workplace and we welcome all applicants regardless of age, ethnicity, gender or cultural background.

